Dr. Peter Toma is a Hungarian-born computer scientist and linguistics researcher. Toma developed and commercialised the SYSTRAN machine translation system. Between 1984 and 1987, approximately, he resided in Dunedin, New Zealand, where he led Textus, a company dedicated to bringing MT to the personal computers that were just being introduced at the time.
